people_also_ask.question: What is bookend in literature?
people_also_ask.heading: “Bookending” is a story-telling device that takes a main or central narrative, and “wraps” it (begins and ends it) with a separate short story. The short story is entirely different from the main narrative, yet supports the overall piece.14-Jun-2017
